# Firefly Asset Gallery conventions

## UI primitives
- Use the shadcn-style primitives in `@/components/ui/*`. Do not introduce
  alternative button, input, or dialog libraries.
- For icons, use `lucide-react` only.
- For client-side animations, use `motion` (the `motion` package), not
  `framer-motion`.

## Styling
- All colors must come from CSS custom properties defined in
  `src/app/globals.css`. Never hardcode hex values in components.
- The `firefly-gradient` class (or `firefly-gradient-text`) is the brand
  treatment — reach for it on hero CTAs and hero typography sparingly so it
  remains a moment of emphasis.
- Use the `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` for composing class lists.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over inline `style` props.

## Images
- Build all image URLs through `picsumUrl()` in `@/lib/picsum.ts`. Never
  inline `picsum.photos` URLs in components.
- Always provide an `alt` value. For decorative images, use `alt=""`.

## State
- Local UI state: `useState`.
- Cross-component client state: extend the Zustand stores in
  `@/lib/store.ts`. Do not create parallel context providers.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on. Avoid `any` — use `unknown` and narrow.
- Imports use the `@/` alias mapped to `./src` from `tsconfig.json`.
